<br>
For one thing,it's not whining---I was just suggesting that there should be more quests for low end weapons and armor.I hate having to buy weapons upgrades(as opposed to quest for them),because the only decent drops pop up in 35+ zones.It's a double standard really---you buy a nice weapon---someone calls you a twink.You ask for new quests that balance weapon improvements in newer expansions with the old world---someone calls you a newbie whiner.An 8/24 may have been a great weapon when everquest first came out,but it's not that great anymore.Besides,with all the twinks running around,newer players are feeling A LOT of pressure to increase their damage output and armor very quickly. The best quest that I have done so far has been the Freeport Reserve Militia Tunic quest,and it yields a decent piece of now drop armor that would have been great 3-4 levels earlier,if the mobs involved with the quest didn't con red to me at the time.I still had a great feeling of accomplishment after finishing the quest,and maybe that's what I'm really getting at---challenging quests that reward you with weapons and armor that you can use at your given level.One of the reasons you don't see many low level players doing quests is the fact that the quests in our level range usually yield No Drop weapons that would have been useful 4-5 levels before we did the quest.I'm not asking for &quot;phat lewt&quot;,or level 10 mobs that drop 20pp,just quests that encourage lower level people to do them.If you do a check on Alakazam,you'll see what I'm talking about---the freeport militia quest was the best one I could find for my class(short of the redemption quest,which I've already started preparing for).I like doing quests---they're a nice diversion from mindless levelling,and you might actually learn something about the history of Norrath by doing them.The only newbies that are seeing benefits from the new expansions are the level 5 people carrying 5kpp,or the alt characters that &quot;borrow&quot; equipment from from their main characters,or new races and classes coming from those expansions.<br>
I will agree that some weapons from the new expansion are way too overpowered for their availabilty,and that keeping the end-game intersting is important for veteran EQ players.I have no problems with that at all.I just see a great value in doing quests for weapons,as it tends to separate the twinks from the people that really care about taking their time,improving their characters gradually,and enjoying the game as their characters mature.If I'm out of line in this way of thinking,please set me straight. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Farvel MacDermott<br>
Dark Elf Rogue of the 20th season<br>
